Checks to see if a path points to a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - The path to check.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host when reading.
password - Password for the user.

Responses\:
failure - The operation failed. The path does not point to a directory.
success - The operation succeeded.
e2382280-182f-4fed-8051-dea8f6fbfd78.787151d5-dd15-42d7-b31c-e895ca25c031.description=
Gets a list of files and folders in a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - The directory to check.
delimiter - A delimiter to put between files and folders in the directory.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host when reading.
password - Password for the user.

Returns\:
The children of the path.

Extra Results\:
count - The number of children.

Responses\:
failure - The operation failed. The path probably could not be found, or was a file.
success - The operation succeeded.
e2382280-182f-4fed-8051-dea8f6fbfd78.af7e7b52-57c3-4d85-81e0-b46c145e6253.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

e2382280-182f-4fed-8051-dea8f6fbfd78.c4ea151f-8f26-44cc-8ec6-bfcfd5e86ca6.transition.description=Unable to read children from directory. e2382280-182f-4fed-8051-dea8f6fbfd78.c81ea388-ac89-4ed7-94f7-d307b5866db0.prompt=Could not read children of ${Source} e2382280-182f-4fed-8051-dea8f6fbfd78.cb4011a6-2968-4432-bca7-53146dbbff73.prompt=Password\: e2382280-182f-4fed-8051-dea8f6fbfd78.dc75c00b-978b-47fd-8c21-ac9d79c2a711.transition.description=processing ${current}. e2382280-182f-4fed-8051-dea8f6fbfd78.description=
This flow will demonstrate how to traverse a directory tree.

Inputs\:
Source - The directory to get the children of.
delimiter - A delimiter to put in between each child of this directory.
username - the username to traverse directories as
password - the password for username

Responses\:
failure - unable to login to host, bad directory name, or filesystem error
success - Operation was successful. Directory was traversed without error


WARNING\: the flow will go through every sub folder of source. If you set source to a folder with many children (such as c\:\ on a windows system) then it will take this flow a long time to complete.
flow.name: Directory Tree Traversal Sample
